cs.IT, cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.NI

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the performance of iterative decoding techniques for linear block codes, which is a topic closely related to information theory. 
2. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper discusses the complexity of iterative decoders achieving optimal performance, which is a topic related to computational complexity. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper introduces the notion of dead-end sets and discusses the trade-off between performance and complexity, which are topics related to data structures and algorithms. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper mentions the Tanner graph, which is a graphical representation of a code and can be used to model social and information networks. 
5. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the performance of iterative decoding techniques, which can be applied to error correction in networking and internet architecture.
